other extensions that get cut

00:18:41.570 --> 00:18:43.100
off, and get ellipsified.

00:18:43.100 --> 00:18:46.680
And that seems to me to be
a really big problem.

00:18:46.680 --> 00:18:52.430
I don't know if that area is
just too small, or if it needs

00:18:52.430 --> 00:18:53.860
some more design thought.

00:18:53.860 --> 00:18:57.290
Or maybe Roman just needs to do
something about third-party

00:18:57.290 --> 00:18:57.940
extensions.

00:18:57.940 --> 00:19:00.500
But as soon as you see ellipses
in that area, you get

00:19:00.500 --> 00:19:01.750
really confused.

00:19:03.830 --> 00:19:10.020
The only other thing that I was
a little bugged about was

00:19:10.020 --> 00:19:14.290
the appearance dialogue, which
I don't have a screenshot of.

00:19:14.290 --> 00:19:16.950
And the reason I don't is
because I've got a lot of

00:19:16.950 --> 00:19:18.810
nitpicks, but they're
all design nits.

00:19:18.810 --> 00:19:20.500
And they don't really
have anything to do

00:19:20.500 --> 00:19:21.510
with The App Clinic.

