00:34:19.590 --> 00:34:24.790
Because we talked about how the
Minimal launcher had an

00:34:24.790 --> 00:34:27.820
app icon that's in the launcher,
so you can get to

00:34:27.820 --> 00:34:29.179
its Settings page.

00:34:29.179 --> 00:34:33.760
Roman's widget does not.

00:34:33.760 --> 00:34:34.370
I think it should.

00:34:34.370 --> 00:34:35.530
What do you think?

00:34:35.530 --> 00:34:37.310
RETO MEIER: I think it's a
really interesting question.

00:34:37.310 --> 00:34:41.489
I think if you're building a
widget which is going to

00:34:41.489 --> 00:34:43.960
target pretty much every Android
device which can have

00:34:43.960 --> 00:34:46.150
widgets, then I think it
probably makes sense to have

00:34:46.150 --> 00:34:47.730
some sort of icon there.

00:34:47.730 --> 00:34:50.530
The challenge or opportunity
with Roman's is that it's only

00:34:50.530 --> 00:34:53.469
available for devices
running Android 4.2.

00:34:53.469 --> 00:34:56.610
And now especially, that tends
to be pretty new phone

00:34:56.610 --> 00:35:00.540
purchases, more of the sort of
upper end of the techie, geeky

00:35:00.540 --> 00:35:02.310
sort of equilibrium.

00:35:02.310 --> 00:35:04.570
So the sorts of people
installing and using the app

00:35:04.570 --> 00:35:07.300
may be more likely to be able to
find the advanced features,

00:35:07.300 --> 00:35:09.560
such as a lock screen widgets.

00:35:09.560 --> 00:35:13.210
So I think it's kind
of a tricky call.

00:35:13.210 --> 00:35:16.270
But yeah, I think some of the
challenges that we talked

00:35:16.270 --> 00:35:19.930
about, the fact that you can't
even give really simple,

00:35:19.930 --> 00:35:22.260
step-by-step instructions on
how to install the widget

00:35:22.260 --> 00:35:25.970
means that, well, if you're the
one who has to explain how

00:35:25.970 --> 00:35:28.920
to install widgets, your chances
of them finding it,

00:35:28.920 --> 00:35:30.770
and finding it useful, probably
are pretty low.

00:35:30.770 --> 00:35:32.420
IAN NI-LEWIS: Yeah, I always
used to hate it when somebody

00:35:32.420 --> 00:35:36.630
would install an icon for
their live wallpaper.

00:35:36.630 --> 00:35:37.660
Right, that--

00:35:37.660 --> 00:35:40.330
